    "The rescaled time is a normalized quantity that allows us to associate an article to a developmental stage of a field (early, peak, or late phase) even when fields have drastically different rise and fall durations.",
    "Denoting by t the time since the first article was published in the field, we fitted the share of articles in the field Ĝ(t) to the equation:G(t) = 1 β e -(t-α)β e -e -(t-α) β (6) using a least-squares optimization fitting procedure.",
    "After obtaining the location α and scale β parameters from the fitting procedure, we computed for each field the re-scaled time:t = t -α β.",
    "( 7)We finally computed for each researcher the minimum RT value achieved across their articles, defining the \"Field age\" feature.Second, we used another independent method to assess the innovative potential of the articles.",
    "This method leverages how disruptive an article is by comparing the attention it receives compared to the articles it cites."
